<article class='well'>
<h1>Great Week for Front-End Articles</h1>
<p>It has been fantastic week for articles about front-end development and structuring CSS. I highly recommend reading all of these to see if there are any things you can pick up or to confirm your way of thinking. <a href="https://medium.com/objects-in-space/f6f404727">Objects in Space</a> by Andrew Colclough, <a href="http://seesparkbox.com/foundry/using_names_to_manage_dozens_of_breakpoints">Mo’ Bears, Mo’ Problems: Using Names To Manage Dozens Of Breakpoints</a> by Ethan Muller, <a href="http://coding.smashingmagazine.com/2013/10/21/challenging-css-best-practices-atomic-approach/">Challenging CSS Best Practices</a> by Thierry Koblentz, <a href="http://www.kapowaz.net/articles/cargo-cult-css">Cargo Cult CSS</a> by Ben Darlow, and <a href="http://adactio.com/journal/6537/">Classy Values</a> by Jeremy Keith.</p>

<p>After all those, here's just a reminder of how far CSS has come: <a href="http://codepen.io/unmeshpro/pen/sDmjc">Friendly Spiral Network</a>.</p>

</article>
</div>
